/users/DirectXMan12","html_url":"https://github.com/DirectXMan12","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DirectXMan12/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DirectXMan12/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DirectXMan12/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DirectXMan12/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DirectXMan12/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DirectXMan12/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DirectXMan12/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DirectXMan12/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DirectXMan12/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2023-08-03T22:48:31Z","updated_at":"2023-08-03T22:48:31Z","body":"I imagined that if you were running `alacritty msg create-window` from an existing instance, you could pass along the window id as an option (e.g. `--inherit-from` from the CLI, `inherit_from: Option<i128>` in the protocol), since we have `$ALACRITTY_WINDOW_ID` already.\r\n\r\nIf you weren't executing from an existing terminal (e.g. a window manager binding), I'd imagine 2 implementation options:\r\n\r\n1. keep track of the \"most recently created\" window, and have a special key that uses that (downsides: if the user sets something on an older window, and then calls create-window from their window manager, this might be confusing)\r\n\r\n2. have a synthetic window id (included in `all` ideally) that represents a \"template config\" that can be specified with `--inherit-from` (upside: likely more consistent user behavior, downside: likely? more complicated, but I haven't actually looked)\r\n\r\nOption 2 seems smoother to me, and a bit nicer, and gives a reasonable set of experiences:\r\n\r\n\r\n1. create-window by itself gives vanilla\r\n2. `config font.size=33`, `create-window --inherit-from self` inherits from the current window\r\n3. `create-window --inherit-from ID` inherits from some specific window\r\n4. `config font.size=33 --window-id=-2`[^1], `create-window --inherit-from template` inherits from the \"template window\"\r\n5. `config font.size=33 --window-id=-1`, `create-window --inherit-from template` also works like (4)\r\n\r\n[^1]: where -2 is the template window, could've just said `-1` if we were cool setting it for all existing windows too","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/alacritty/alacritty/issues/comments/1664733071/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"DirectXMan12","id":119737,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjExOTczNw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/119737?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/DirectXMan12","html_url":"https://github.com/DirectXMan12","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DirectXMan12/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DirectXMan12/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DirectXMan12/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DirectXMan12/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DirectXMan12/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DirectXMan12/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DirectXMan12/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DirectXMan12/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DirectXMan12/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/alacritty/alacritty/issues/comments/1666601339","html_url":"https://github.com/alacritty/alacritty/issues/7128#issuecomment-1666601339","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/alacritty/alacritty/issues/7128","id":1666601339,"node_id":"IC_kwDOAxkop85jVlF7","user":{"login":"chrisduerr","id":8886672,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg4ODY2NzI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/8886672?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/chrisduerr","html_url":"https://github.com/chrisduerr","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/chrisduerr/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/chrisduerr/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/chrisduerr/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/chrisduerr/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/chrisduerr/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/chrisduerr/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/chrisduerr/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/chrisduerr/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/chrisduerr/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2023-08-05T20:46:41Z","updated_at":"2023-08-05T20:46:41Z","body":"> I imagined that if you were running alacritty msg create-window from an existing instance, you could pass along the window id as an option (e.g. --inherit-from from the CLI, inherit_from: Option<i128> in the protocol), since we have $ALACRITTY_WINDOW_ID already.\r\n\r\nCopying from arbitrary windows is a massive clusterfuck and not an option imo.\r\n\r\n> have a synthetic window id (included in all ideally) that represents a \"template config\" that can be specified with --inherit-from (upside: likely more consistent user behavior, downside: likely? more complicated, but I haven't actually looked)\r\n\r\nAlso an absolute mess that will definitely not happen.\r\n\r\nI can imagine this getting implemented by differentiating between options set for `-1` and specific window IDs and having new windows inherit existing options set for `-1`. I'd assume that should work for you?","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url